    "about_page": {
      "founder_story": "Founder Story",
      "view_more": "View More",
      "about_ana_uzelac": "About Ana Uzelac",
      "ana_uzelac_description_1": "Ana Uzelac is a visual artist who paints directly on silk. Each scarf from AHA by Ana Uzelac begins as a hand-painted artwork, later transformed into a luxurious, wearable piece through a meticulous reproduction process.",
      "ana_uzelac_description_2": "AHA is an artist-led brand rooted in authenticity, artistic integrity, and emotional connection. Every scarf is a faithful reproduction of an original silk painting - printed in France on fine silk twill and finished by hand with exceptional care.",
      "ana_uzelac_description_3": "Ana created AHA to bridge the gap between fine art and fashion - offering scarves that are both collectible and personal. These are not mass-produced accessories, but statement pieces meant to be worn boldly and lived in fully.",
      "ana_uzelac_description_4": "With Ana involved in every step - from the initial brushstroke to the final fold - each scarf carries her story, energy, and vision. AHA is more than a label; it's wearable art for those who appreciate meaning, craftsmanship, and individuality.",
      "explore_collections": "Explore Collections",
      "ana_uzelac": "Ana Uzelac",
      "moodboard": "MOODBOARD",
      "work_in_progress": "WORK in Progress",
      "why_it_matters": "Why It Matters?",
      "why_it_matters_description_1": "In a world of mass production, AHA by Ana Uzelac stands for intimacy, intention, and the handmade. These scarves are not seasonal products or fleeting trends - they are moments captured in silk.",
      "why_it_matters_description_2": "Each piece carries the warmth of the artist’s hand and the weight of a story worth keeping. They are not just accessories, but quiet acts of resistance against the algorithm - reminders that beauty doesn’t have to shout to be seen.",
      "why_it_matters_description_3": "In the age of automation, human presence is rare - and therefore, valuable. AHA scarves carry that presence. In texture, in color, in soul.",
      "a_different_kind_of_luxury": "A Different Kind of Luxury",
      "a_different_kind_of_luxury_description_1": "AHA is not for everyone - and that’s the point. It’s for those who collect with their heart, who feel the difference between a logo and a life story. For those who pause in galleries just a little longer. Who touch fabric like they’re reading with their hands. Who crave something that speaks not louder, but truer.",
      "a_different_kind_of_luxury_description_2": "It’s for those who believe in slowness as luxury - in objects that breathe, that carry the trace of time, of care, of soul. Who find value not in perfection, but in presence. Who want to wear something that feels alive.",
      "a_different_kind_of_luxury_description_3": "AHA scarves are not just things to be owned - they’re experiences to return to. A certain color that reminds you of a place. A fold that echoes a feeling. A gift to yourself that turns into a memory with someone else.",
      "a_different_kind_of_luxury_description_4": "Each scarf is a future heirloom. Not because it’s expensive, but because it meant something. It was chosen with emotion. Worn through seasons. Kept close. And, eventually, passed on - carrying with it not just the artist’s story, but yours.",
      "art_that_finds_you": "Art That Finds You",
      "art_that_finds_you_description_1": "There is a quiet dialogue between the woman who paints and the woman who wears. Though they may never meet, they are connected - through color, through gesture, through the shared understanding that beauty can be both soft and strong.",
      "art_that_finds_you_description_2": "An AHA scarf becomes a continuation of the artist’s voice - shaped now by the rhythm of another life, another body, another story. It is art not preserved behind glass, but released into the world - to move, to witness, to belong."
    },
